89 SECTION 4.
90 Said chapter is further amended in Code Section 48-5-45, relating to application for
91 homestead exemption and unlawful to solicit fee to file application for homestead for
92 another, by revising subsection (a) as follows:
93 "(a)(1) An applicant seeking a homestead exemption as provided in Code
94 Section 48-5-44 and qualifying under the provisions of Code Section 48-5-40 shall file
95 a written application and schedule with the tax receiver or tax commissioner charged with
96 the duty of receiving returns of property for taxation at any time during the calendar year
97 subsequent to the property becoming the primary residence of the applicant up to and
98 including the date for the closing of the books for the return of taxes for the calendar year,
99 except that, in the case of a property which is subject to a reassessment by the board of
100 tax assessors, such application and schedule may be filed in conjunction with or in lieu
101 of an appeal of the reassessment.
102 (2) The failure to file properly the application and schedule on or before the date for the
103 closing of the books for the return of taxes of a calendar year in which the taxes are due
104 shall constitute a waiver of the homestead exemption on the part of the applicant failing
105 to make the application for such exemption for that year."
